 is consistent with formaldehyde\nforming in the ice as soon as CO has frozen onto the grains, with most of the\ndeuteration happening towards the end of the prestellar core phase. A\ncomparison with available time-dependent chemical models indicates that the\nsource is in the early Class 0 stage.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 15 Nov 2017 13:24:17 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-02-28"}
